modules.description: This module implements a random forest classifier trained on integer-based datasets, producing predictions as categorical outputs. It provides functions to generate forests in parallel, classify data, and persist models to disk. Concrete use cases include building scalable decision tree ensembles for classification tasks and deploying trained models in production environments via file serialization.

Implements random forest generation and classification for C4.5 decision trees. It operates on training sets and data vectors defined by the parameter module `X`, producing forests of decision trees for supervised learning tasks. This module trains models, classifies new data points, and persists trained forests to disk for later use in prediction workflows.

This module implements a random forest classifier for numerical data, generating models from training sets and classifying new data points. It provides functions to build forests in parallel, classify data, and export or load models from disk. Concrete use cases include machine learning classification tasks on structured numerical datasets, such as predicting categories from sensor data or financial metrics.

This module implements random forest generation and classification for decision trees, operating on training sets and data vectors from the parameter module. It provides functions to train models, classify new data points, and persist forests to disk. Concrete use cases include building scalable ensembles for classification tasks on structured datasets and deploying trained models in production environments via file serialization.

Implements random forest generation and classification for decision trees, working with training sets and data vectors. Provides functions to train models, classify new data points, and serialize forests to disk. Used for building scalable ensembles on structured datasets and deploying models in production via file persistence.
